00:03:42.894 --> 00:03:43.560
ERICA MORSE: Hi.

00:03:43.560 --> 00:03:44.226
My name's Erica.

00:03:44.226 --> 00:03:45.770
I'm a designer on
the Cardboard team,

00:03:45.770 --> 00:03:47.436
and today I'm going
to be talking to you

00:03:47.436 --> 00:03:49.115
about why virtual reality.

00:03:52.059 --> 00:03:53.600
With virtual reality,
you give people

00:03:53.600 --> 00:03:55.887
one of the most popular
superpowers, teleportation.

00:03:59.240 --> 00:04:00.980
Imagine your third
grade self learning

00:04:00.980 --> 00:04:03.770
about the Mayan civilization
for the first time,

00:04:03.770 --> 00:04:05.830
but instead of
looking at a textbook,

00:04:05.830 --> 00:04:08.596
you're standing at the
base of Chichen Itza.

00:04:08.596 --> 00:04:10.470
This is actually imagery
from the expeditions

00:04:10.470 --> 00:04:12.670
that we announced at
yesterday's keynote.

00:04:12.670 --> 00:04:15.240
Soon, teachers will actually
be able to take their students

00:04:15.240 --> 00:04:17.660
on virtual tours
around these ruins.

00:04:17.660 --> 00:04:22.490
Think about how much more
fun school is going to be.

00:04:22.490 --> 00:04:25.370
VR also allows for more
engaging journalism.

00:04:25.370 --> 00:04:27.790
Instead of reading about the
earthquake in Nepal, what

00:04:27.790 --> 00:04:29.240
if you could go
there and see what

00:04:29.240 --> 00:04:31.530
it's like firsthand
on the ground?

00:04:31.530 --> 00:04:33.830
Think about the empathy
and sense of civic duty

00:04:33.830 --> 00:04:36.670
this could inspire.

00:04:36.670 --> 00:04:38.780
And finally, how
about the art world?

00:04:38.780 --> 00:04:41.800
Installations that play
with space, light, and color

00:04:41.800 --> 00:04:44.900
can only be fully appreciated
in person, or now,

00:04:44.900 --> 00:04:46.740
in virtual reality.

00:04:46.740 --> 00:04:49.800
So you can transport your users.

00:04:49.800 --> 00:04:51.510
You can also give
them experiences

00:04:51.510 --> 00:04:56.010
that are physically
impossible in the real world.

00:04:56.010 --> 00:05:01.710
How about flying, another
popular superpower?

00:05:01.710 --> 00:05:04.570
In a Cardboard app
called Caaaaardboard!--

00:05:04.570 --> 00:05:07.030
