00:38:27.434 --> 00:38:28.100
JON WILEY: Yeah.

00:38:28.100 --> 00:38:32.224
I think there's a spectrum
of capability of devices

00:38:32.224 --> 00:38:34.390
out there, and so taking
into account the capability

00:38:34.390 --> 00:38:37.060
of the device is important.

00:38:37.060 --> 00:38:42.000
For Cardboard, we tend to
think of it as snackable VR.

00:38:42.000 --> 00:38:45.400
It's not for long
duration experiences.

00:38:45.400 --> 00:38:48.250
Really, if you're going
to, as I was saying

00:38:48.250 --> 00:38:53.990
at the very top of it, which is
every capability that you add

00:38:53.990 --> 00:38:58.030
increases the constraints
around making sure

00:38:58.030 --> 00:39:01.650
it's golden in terms
of the experience.

00:39:01.650 --> 00:39:04.640
And so you can create
a richer experience

00:39:04.640 --> 00:39:07.817
with a more capable
device, but you just

00:39:07.817 --> 00:39:09.650
have to be extra, extra
careful to make sure

00:39:09.650 --> 00:39:11.320
that the experiences
is really living up

00:39:11.320 --> 00:39:13.620
to the expectations
of the device.

00:39:13.620 --> 00:39:17.200
So with devices like
Cardboard, at least today,

00:39:17.200 --> 00:39:19.850
given today's mobile
phone technology,

00:39:19.850 --> 00:39:21.320
it doesn't have
the full six degree

00:39:21.320 --> 00:39:24.664
of freedom tracking that
you move around in a space,

00:39:24.664 --> 00:39:26.330
so you just have to
be cognizant of that

00:39:26.330 --> 00:39:28.330
and designing for the
limitations of the device.

00:39:28.330 --> 00:39:30.630
I actually think
that the best designs

00:39:30.630 --> 00:39:34.210
come from not working
against the system

00:39:34.210 --> 00:39:36.977
but working with the system
to create a good experience.

00:39:36.977 --> 00:39:39.060
And so if you've got a
high end system that you're

00:39:39.060 --> 00:39:40.850
designing for, that's awesome.

00:39:40.850 --> 00:39:42.897
You can create amazing content.

00:39:42.897 --> 00:39:44.480
But I still think
that amazing content

00:39:44.480 --> 00:39:48.760
can be created on more
restrictive systems

00:39:48.760 --> 00:39:52.840
if it's playing to the
strengths of that system.

